            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just have a look at the many youtube videos\r\n\r\nSome do everything in init.lua some have lua/core/{plugins, plugin_config, utils} some have lua{config, options, plugins} it's all over the place.  Some have init.lua sprinkled between folders, some do it all in one.  Makes it very confusing for new users.\r\n\r\nJust look at nvim.autopairs for example, it's not clear how it all goes together, Lazyvim, Lunarvim mini.nvim nvchad all handle things differently.  Very difficult to get clear examples that actually work.\r\n\r\nMany times one can follow a video but then have a super hard time getting a plugin to work because it doesn't provide a standard working example from options to setup() to require etc.\r\n",
